{"build_type":"executable","description":"Run a long program in the background with its output captured to a file, returning immediately instead of blocking the caller. Request: program (binary path), request (the JSON request object handed to the program as argv index one, rendered to a cstring), log (file path to receive stdout+stderr). Opens the log truncating, forks, the child redirects fd 1 and fd 2 onto the log and execve-s the program (empty environment; exit_group 1 if execve fails), the parent closes its log handle and returns {pid, log} without waiting. The caller then reads the log file to see the output once the program has finished (poll a side effect such as the new generation, then read the log). The background-long-process workflow without a server-side change.","module_name":"launch-detached-program-recording-output-toward-file","package_name":"launch-detached-program-recording-output-toward-file","function_definitions":{"launch-detached-program-recording-output-toward-file":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"sixteen","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":16},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"twentyfour","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":24},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"k_program","variable_type":"str","assignment_oper